Strictly adhere with the provisions of RA No. 9184 and its revised IRR;

Strengthen internal control over procurement activities especially in the role of the BAC;

Make payments thru checks and only payments in small amounts may be made by cash through the petty cash fund. See to it all receipts were deducted with corresponding withholding tax; and 

Require the Municipal Accountant to withhold taxes due the government in accordance with the BIR regulations for those official receipts not deducted with corresponding withholding tax.

Direct the AO and the Accountant to prepare and submit required reports namely; RCI, the ROD, with all the originals of vouchers/payrolls and all supporting documents showing utilization of funds within fifteen (15) days after the end of each month;

Include all the projects, programs and activities under the Fund Transfers in the Quarterly Accomplishment Report submitted by the Municipality to be subject for inspection and validation, or upon completion submit written request for inspection to the Office of the Auditor; and

Cause immediate refund of the unutilized balance of the Fund Transfers to the SA concerned.

Strictly implement and monitor the imposition of fines and penalties enumerated in the municipal ordinance as mandated under RA 9003;

Ensure proper issuance of Citation Tickets to  violators to yield  increase in revenue and effectively maintain cleanliness in the Municipality; and

Post tarpaulins/billboards in conspicuous places within the Municipality indicating the ordinance and the penal sanctions in case of violation so that the public may be informed.

a. Initiate the payment of employees’ salaries, allowances, fringe benefits and other emoluments through the bank as a means of improving fiscal management in accordance with Section 4(8) and 2 of PD 1445, with the expected result of minimizing the attendant risks identified with cash-paid payrolls and easing the effects of manpower attrition;
b. Make representation/ arrangement with any government bank like the LBP or the PVB for an opening of individual ATM savings accounts by the employees through a Memorandum of Agreement (MOA); and
c. Adopt the payroll-thru-bank scheme upon approval of the MOA to strengthen fiscal management.

a. Amend the contract through the Sangguniang Bayan to include in the terms and conditions the requirement for guaranty deposits to ensure that the Municipality is secured from any unwarranted unpaid rentals;
b. Direct the Assistant Municipal Treasurer to secure and keep all contracts pertaining to existing market stall lease;
c. Direct the AMT to require the lessee to pay the corresponding unpaid monthly rentals, penalty/ies and interests before any renewal of the contract in their favor;
d. Direct the Municipal Accountant to maintain complete subsidiary ledgers of all lessees/occupants to monitor any uncollected market rentals; and
e. Direct the AMT to monitor strictly the implementation of the terms and conditions of the contract especially in the prompt payment of rent and the imposition and collection of penalties and interest upon failure to pay on time.
